y lap,  the red straw,  poking into my chin,  impresses a small ''o'' into sun-kissed skin.  i clutch my rainbow change purse,  its interior pink plastic  and play currency.  my nostrils flare in delight as my belly laughs and i sit in the red radio flyer.  in blissful carelessness i think,  i am the happiest girl in the world. 
